    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I get that it's a debate, but some say that treating it as just 'one side of a debate' is a bit dangerous. If we ignore the possibility of a catastrophic event just because it's not 'settled' yet, aren't we basically gambling with humanity? Shouldn't the precautionary principle take precedence when the stakes are this high?",
